{
  "text": "The overall patterns of expression of proteases or protease-inhibitors does not differ substantially between sporocysts in untreated and niclosamide-treated snails (Fig 5) . When specific proteases like elastases, leishmanolysins, and cathepsins are examined, some changes in expression were noted. Niclosamide-exposed sporocysts exhibited modest increases in expression of cercarial elastases SmCE1a, SmCE1a.2, cercarial protease, and SmCE2b (Fig 5) . The SmCE isoforms represent an expanded family of elastases unique to some Schistosoma species including S. mansoni [CITATION_1] . Transcripts for leishmanolysins which are metalloproteases also known as invadolysins [CITATION_2] , also exhibited a modest increase in representation in niclosamide-exposed sporocysts as compared to untreated sporocysts [CITATION_3] .",
  "correct_citation": {
